The paper discusses the current landscape and future of Internet Protocol television experiences, including operator-based, over-the-top, and user-generated content. It also addresses new services like social TV and recommendation engines, dissemination including new paradigms built on peer-to-peer and content-centric networks, as well as the quality of experience. These topics are relevant to several sub-categories, including Multimedia (cs.MM), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC), and Computers and Society (cs.CY).
